ya%2C%20located%20in%20Nagoya%2C%20kimono-dressed%20waitresses%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fx.com%2Fbangkoklad%2Fstatus%2F1729710012539261087%3Fs%3D20%5C%22%3E%20slap%20a%20willing%20customer%20i%3C%2Fa%3En%20the%20face%20with%20their%20palms%2C%20over%20and%20over%20again%20for%20300%20Japanese%20Yen%20(Rs%20170).%20There's%20also%20a%20500%20yen%20(Rs%20283)%20surcharge%20if%20patrons%20request%20a%20specific%20staff%20member%20to%20slap%20them.%20The%20service%20is%20popular%20with%20both%20Japanese%20men%20and%20women%2C%20as%20well%20as%20foreign%20tourists.%20Many%20even%20express%20gratitude%20to%20the%20waitresses%20for%20the%20brutal%20service.%20However%2C%20after%20videos%20of%20the%20bizarre%20practice%20went%20viral%20online%2C%20the%20restaurant%20took%20to%20X%20to%20inform%20that%20the%20restaurant%20does%20not%20offer%20slaps%20anymore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20post%20on%20the%20microblogging%20website%2C%20they%20wrote%2C%20%26quot%3BShachihoko-ya%20currently%20does%20not%20offer%20slaps.%20We%20appreciate%20the%20attention%20it%20has%20received%20today%2C%20but%20we%20cannot%20accommodate%20visits%20with%20the%20intention%20of%20receiving%20slaps.%20We%20didn't%20expect%20old%20videos%20to%20go%20viral%20like%20this%2C%20so%20please%20understand%20before%20coming.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20the%20controversial%20service%2C%20which%20started%20in%202012%2C%20revived%20the%20establishment's%20business%2C%20attracting%20an%20increasing%20number%20of%20patrons%20willing%20to%20try%20the%20experience.%20Initially%2C%20only%20one%20female%20staff%20member%20did%20the%20slapping.%20As%20demand%20grew%2C%20management%20hired%20several%20girls%20willing%20to%20dish%20out%20some%20slaps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20clear%20whether%20the%20service%20has%20been%20permanently%20discontinued%20or%20will%20be%20back%20soon.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Japan%20has%20another%20interesting%20restaurant%20where%20customers%20receive%20something%20which%20they%20did%20not%20order.%20This%20situation%20is%20almost%20a%20norm%2C%20rather%20than%20a%20sign%20of%20negligence%20at%20the%20'Restaurant%20of%20Mistaken%20Orders'.%20Here%2C%20the%20waiters%20don't%20find%20themselves%20in%20trouble%20when%20they%20serve%20a%20different%20dish.%20They%20are%20expected%20to.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJapanese%20television%20director%20Shiro%20Oguni%20aimed%20to%20change%20people's%20perceptions%20about%20ageing%20and%20the%20intricate%20issues%20it%20entails.%20He%20wanted%20to%20explicitly%20tackle%20dementia%20as%20a%20cognitive%20issue.%20He%20devised%20a%20brilliant%20plan%20to%20challenge%20people's%20beliefs%20regarding%20the%20same.%20In%20the%20concept%20movie%20for%20the%20project%2C%20he%20explains%2C%20%26quot%3BDementia%20is%20so%20widely%20misunderstood.%20People%20believe%20you%20can't%20do%20anything%20for%20yourself.%20And%20the%20condition%20will%20often%20mean%20complete%20isolation%20from%20society.%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0When%20one%20attends%20a%20pop-up%20of%20the%20restaurant%2C%20one%20will%20find%20that%20the%20waiting%20staff%20is%20solely%20composed%20of%20people%20suffering%20from%20dementia.%20Diners%20are%20thus%20obliged%20to%20interact%20and%20confront%20their%20preconceptions%20about%20this%20condition.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20waiters%20might%20decide%20to%20eat%20with%20the%20customers%2C%20present%20orders%20unexpectedly%2C%20or%20even%20forget%20what%20was%20ordered.%20It%20is%20suggested%20that%20diners%20react%20with%20warmth%20and%20humour.%20The%20project%20fully%20embraces%20the%20humorous%20aspects%20of%20sometimes%20getting%20the%20order%20wrong.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701961980000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-12%2Fnvgh1mdo_japan-restaurant_625x300_07_December_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Foffbeat%2Fjapan-eatery-where-people-pay-to-get-slapped-by-waitresses-stops-bizarre-service-4643517%22%2C%2