C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20special%20report%20was%20published%20on%20November%2016%2C%202023%20and%20was%20titled%2C%20%E2%80%98How%20an%20Indian%20Startup%20Hacked%20the%20World%E2%80%99.%20It%20claimed%20that%20the%20Delhi-based%20firm%20Appin%2C%20which%20was%20started%20by%20brothers%20Rajat%20and%20Anuj%20Khare%2C%20allegedly%20hacked%20on%20an%20industrial%20scale%2C%20stealing%20data%20from%20political%20leaders%2C%20international%20executives%2C%20prominent%20attorneys%20and%20more.%20Reuters%20described%20its%20activity%20as%20a%20%E2%80%9Csprawling%20cyber-mercenary%20operation%20that%20extended%20across%20the%20world.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Finvestigates%2Fspecial-report%2Fusa-hackers-appin%2F%5C%22%3EEditor%E2%80%99s%20note%3C%2Fa%3E%20published%20on%20December%205%2C%20Reuters%20said%20it%20had%20temporarily%20removed%20the%20article%20to%20comply%20with%20a%20preliminary%20court%20order%20issued%20on%20December%204.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20order%2C%20additional%20district%20judge%20Rakesh%20Kumar%20Singh%20noted%20that%20he%20was%20prima%20facie%20satisfied%20that%20the%20special%20report%20was%20%E2%80%9Cindicative%20of%20defamation%2C%E2%80%9D%20and%20that%20the%20website%20should%20not%20retain%20such%20an%20article%20in%20the%20public%20domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%2C%20however%2C%20clarified%20that%20this%20was%20only%20a%20prima%20facie%20opinion.%20The%20%E2%80%9Cdefendants%20shall%20have%20sufficient%20opportunity%20to%20express%20their%20views%20through%20reply%2C%20contest%20in%20the%20main%20suit%20etc.%20and%20the%20final%20decision%20shall%20be%20taken%20subsequently.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20court%20order%20was%20issued%20amid%20a%20pending%20lawsuit%20brought%20against%20Reuters%20in%20November%202022%20by%20the%20lawyers%20of%20Appin%20Association%20of%20Training%20Centre%2C%20accusing%20the%20news%20agency%20of%20a%20defamatory%20campaign.%20%E2%80%9CAs%20set%20forth%20in%20its%20court%20filings%2C%20Reuters%20disputes%20those%20claims%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20agency%20stated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Reuters%20report%20claimed%20its%20investigation%20found%20that%20Appin%20grew%20from%20an%20educational%20startup%20to%20%E2%80%9Ca%20hack-for-hire%20powerhouse%E2%80%9D.%20Appin%20alumni%20went%20on%20to%20form%20other%20firms%20that%20are%20still%20active%2C%20the%20report%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20said%20that%20Khare%20was%20a%2020-year-old%20computer%20science%20student%20when%20he%20and%20his%20friends%20came%20up%20with%20the%20idea%20for%20Appin%20in%202003.%20They%20launched%20their%20first%20classes%20on%20computer%20programming.%20By%202005%2C%20the%20company%20had%20an%20office%20in%20west%20Delhi.%20Soon%2C%20he%20took%20charge%20of%20the%20firm%20with%20his%20brother%20Anuj%2C%20a%20motivational%20speaker%20who%20returned%20to%20India%20after%20a%20stint%20running%20a%20startup%20in%20Texas%2C%20Reuters%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajat%20Khare%E2%80%99s%20US%20representative%2C%20the%20law%20firm%20Clare%20Locke%2C%20rejected%20any%20association%20between%20its%20client%20and%20the%20cyber-mercenary%20business.%20It%20told%20Reuters%20that%20Khare%20%E2%80%9Chas%20never%20operated%20or%20supported%2C%20and%20certainly%20did%20not%20create%2C%20any%20illegal%20%E2%80%98hack%20for%20hire%E2%80%99%20industry%20in%20India%20or%20anywhere%20else.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClare%20Locke%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMr.%20Khare%20has%20dedicated%20much%20of%20his%20career%20to%20the%20fields%20of%20information%20technology%20security%20%E2%80%93%20that%20is%2C%20cyber-defense%20and%20the%20prevention%20of%20illicit%20hacking.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20noted%20that%20while%20the%20original%20Appin%20has%20now%20largely%20disappeared%20from%20public%20view%20its%20impact%20was%20still%20felt%20today%2C%20as%20copycat%20firms%20led%20by%20its%20alumni%20continue%20to%20target%20thousands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhare%E2%80%99s%20lawyers%20said%20media%20articles%20tying%20him%20to%20hacking%20were%20%E2%80%9Cfalse%E2%80%9D%20or%20%E2%80%9Cfundamentally%20flawed.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EClare%20Locke%2C%20as%20quoted%20in%20the%20report%2C%20said%20under%20Khare%E2%80%99s%20tenure%2C%20Appin%20specialised%20in%20training%20thousands%20of%20students%20in%20cybersecurity%2C%20robotics%20and%20artificial%20intelligence%2C%20%E2%80%9Cnever%20in%20illicit%20hacking.%E2%80%9D%20The%20lawyers%20said%20Khare%20left%20Appin%2C%20in%20part%2C%20because%20rogue%20actors%20were%20operating%20under%20the%20company%E2%80%99s%20brand%2C%20and%20he%20wanted%20%E2%80%9Cto%20avoid%20the%20appearance%20of%20associations%20with%20people%20who%20were%20misusing%20the%20Appin%20name.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Delhi%20district%20judge%2C%20while%20ordering%20Reuters%20to%20take%20down%20the%20article%2C%20said%20the%20%E2%80%9Cbalance%20of%20convenience%E2%80%9D%20lies%20in%20directing%20the%20withdrawal%20of%20the%20content.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20am%20of%20the%20opinion%20that%20even%20if%20the%20defendants%20for%20some%20period%20do%20not%20retain%20the%20article%20on%20the%20website%20and%20on%20that%20account%20they%20suffer%20any%20market%20value%2C%20%5Bthey%5D%20can%20be%20ultimately%20compensated%20by%20money%20from%20the%20plaintiff%20but%20the%20retention%20of%20such%20material%20on%20the%20website%20if%20allowed%2C%20the%20same%20may%20have%20devastating%20effect%20on%20the%20general%20students%20population%20of%20India%20(sic)%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20court%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20said%20its%20report%20on%20Appin%20was%20based%20on%20thousands%20of%20company%20emails%20as%20well%20as%20financial%20records%2C%20presentations%2C%20photos%20and%20instant%20messages%20from%20the%20firm.%20Reporters%20also%20reviewed%20case%20files%20from%20American%2C%20Norwegian%2C%20Dominican%20and%20Swiss%20law%20enforcement%2C%20and%20interviewed%20dozens%20of%20former%20Appin%20employees%20and%20hundreds%20of%20victims%20of%20India-based%20hackers%2C%20it%20said.%20The%20reporters%20gathered%20the%20material%20%E2%80%93%20which%20spans%202005%20until%20earlier%20this%20year%20%E2%80%93%20from%20ex-employees%2C%20clients%20and%20security%20professionals%20who%E2%80%99ve%20studied%20the%20company%2C%20the%20agency%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EReuters%20said%20it%20verified%20the%20authenticity%20of%20the%20Appin%20communications%20with%2015%20people%2C%20including%20private%20investigators%20who%20commissioned%20hacks%20and%20ex-Appin%20hackers%20themselves.%20The%20news%20agency%20also%20asked%20US%20cybersecurity%20firm%20SentinelOne%20to%20review%20the%20material%20for%20signs%20that%20it%20had%20been%20digitally%20altered.%20The%20firm%20said%20it%20found%20none%2C%20according%20to%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701957613000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F07184417%2F2493267536_f12b7eef35_h.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-court-reuters-takes-down-story-indian-firm-hacking%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20additional%20district%20judge%20North%20West%20Rohini%20court%20found%20the%20article%20to%20be%20prima%20facie%20%E2%80%9Cindicative%20of%20defamation%E2%80%9D.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fdelhi-court-reuters-takes-down-story-indian-firm-hacking%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Alia%2C%20Neetu%20react%20to%20Soni%20Razdan's%20video%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701957252000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-105817445%2Cimgsize-40240.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fsoni-razdan-shares-a-glimpse-of-her-christmas-tree-adorned-with-customise