23120700888_1.html%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Debate%3A%20Yogendra%20Yadav's%20Analysis%20Downplaying%20BJP%20Wins%20in%20Assembly%20Polls%20Is%20Misleading%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F11%2FModi-Shah.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ENote%3A%20Yogendra%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20response%20to%20this%20piece%20is%20appended%20below.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYogendra%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20intervention%20through%20his%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-assembly-elections-hat-trick-2024%5C%22%3Earticle%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DKKn2SPGOUkc%26t%3D76s%5C%22%3Evideo%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%20%3C%2Fem%3Eto%20control%20the%20damage%20from%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20psychological%20warfare%E2%80%9D%20unleashed%20by%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20after%20the%20assembly%20election%20results%20are%20well-intentioned%20but%20misleading%2C%20both%20on%20facts%20and%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20of%20his%20four%20arguments%20to%20substantiate%20his%20claim%20%E2%80%93%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9CBJP%E2%80%99s%20victory%20is%20not%20so%20big%2C%20and%20Congress%20fall%20is%20not%20so%20deep%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20suffer%20from%20selective%20facts%20and%20subjective%20interpretation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20of%20the%20responses%20to%20the%20election%20results%20from%20the%20progressive%20camp%20are%20as%20surprising%20as%20the%20results.%20Some%20scholars%20like%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fprogressives-stop-hectoring-india-parties%5C%22%3EPushparaj%20Deshpande%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20calling%20for%20self-censorship%20in%20publicly%20criticising%20Congress%20over%20its%20lacunae%20and%20acting%20as%20social%20evangelicals%20among%20the%20traditional%20vote%20base%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20providing%20the%20last%20mile%20connectivity%20that%20the%20Congress%20lacks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbjp-assembly-elections-hat-trick-2024%5C%22%3EThe%20Myth%20of%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Hat-Trick%20and%20What%20the%20Statistics%20Really%20Say%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOthers%20like%20Yadav%20are%20ignoring%20the%20political%20and%20ideological%20inefficacy%20of%20the%20Congress%20as%20an%20electoral%20opposition%20to%20the%20BJP.%20Both%20these%20approaches%20might%20provide%20false%20comfort%20to%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20secular%20camp%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20however%2C%20they%20help%20the%20onward%20march%20of%20the%20Hindutva%20juggernaut.%20This%20is%20why%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20reading%20of%20the%20election%20results%20demands%20close%20scrutiny.%20Let%20us%20dissect%20them%20one%20by%20one.%3Cu%3E%20%3C%2Fu%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDid%20the%20Congress%20gain%209%20lakh%20more%20votes%2C%20or%2050%20lakh%20less%20than%20the%20BJP%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20bid%20to%20boost%20the%20morale%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20those%20opposed%20to%20Hindutva%20politics%2C%20Yadav%20observes%20that%20the%20total%20number%20of%20votes%20that%20the%20Congress%20polled%20against%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20four%20states%20should%20bring%20solace.%20All%20the%20votes%20the%20Congress%20procured%20in%20the%20four%20states%2C%20namely%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Telangana%2C%20worked%20out%20to%20be%204.9%20crore%20whereas%20the%20BJP%20got%20only%204.81%20crore.%20Hence%20the%20analysis%20that%20despite%20Congress%20losing%20three%20states%2C%20its%20vote%20share%20is%20higher%20by%209%20lakh%20than%20the%20BJP.%20Thus%2C%20the%20conclusion%20is%20that%20people%20still%20prefer%20Congress%20though%20it%20lost%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20a%20mathematically%20correct%20but%20politically%20incorrect%20conclusion.%20It%20is%20for%20a%20simple%20reason%20that%20it%20includes%20Telangana%20in%20its%20overall%20vote%20calculation%20along%20with%20the%20three%20Hindi%20states.%20In%20Telangana%2C%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20fight%20was%20primarily%20against%20the%20Bharat%20Rasthra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%2C%20not%20the%20BJP.%20The%20inclusion%20of%20Telangana%20in%20the%20overall%20calculation%20completely%20glosses%20over%20the%20dismal%20performance%20of%20Congress%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20and%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27132111%2FThe-Wire-91.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27132111%2FThe-Wire-91.png%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27132111%2FThe-Wire-91-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F27132111%2FThe-Wire-91-1024x478.png%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-686533%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22560%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECongress%20leaders%20Mallu%20Bhatti%20Vikramarka%2C%20Revanth%20Reddy%2C%20Priyanka%20Gandhi%20Vadra%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20among%20others.%20Photo%3A%20Twitter%2F%40INCIndia%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20we%20exclude%20Telangana%2C%20the%20number%20of%20votes%20the%20Congress%20obtained%20in%20the%20three%20Hindi%20states%20is%203%2C98%2C42%2C%20115%20while%20the%20BJP%20polled%204%2C48%2C%2075%2C%20952.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20the%20BJP%20procured%2050%20lakh%20votes%20more%20than%20the%20Congress%20in%20these%20three%20states.%20However%2C%20if%20we%20include%20Telangana%2C%20the%20picture%20changes%20and%20hence%20provides%20false%20comfort.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-bharat-rashtra-samithi-congress-kcr%5C%22%3EIn%20Telangana%2C%20Five%20Trends%20Highlight%20Divides%2C%20Gains%2C%20Losses%20and%20Blows%20to%20Expansion%20Plans%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIf%20you%20compare%20the%20same%20with%20the%202018%20elections%2C%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20predicament%C2%A0becomes%20more%20stark.%20In%20the%20previous%20election%2C%20the%20BJP%20obtained%203.41%20crore%20votes%20from%20these%20three%20states%20and%20Congress%203.57%20crore%20votes.%20Thus%20compared%20to%202018%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20tally%20rose%20by%201%20crore.%20The%20Congress%20could%20increase%20its%20tally%20by%20only%2047%20lakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Centre%20for%20the%20Study%20of%20Developing%20Societies%20(CSDS)%20survey%20and%20the%20earlier%20Axis%20survey%20suggest%20that%20most%20of%20these%20new%20BJP%20voters%20happen%20to%20be%20from%20the%20Other%20Backward%20Classes%20(OBCs)%20and%20even%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(STs).%20This%20means%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20social%20base%20is%20eroding%2C%20further%20giving%20way%20to%20the%20BJP.%20This%20is%20a%20dangerous%20portent%20and%20would%20never%20be%20acknowledged%20if%20one%20takes%20comfort%20in%20the%20misleading%20figure%20of%20a%209%20lakh%20vote%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%2C%20clubbing%20Telangana%20with%20the%20three%20heartland%20states%20and%20concluding%20that%20the%20Congress%20got%209%20lakh%20more%20votes%20than%20the%20BJP%20will%20prevent%20the%20former%20from%20identifying%20the%20steep%20slide%20due%20to%20its%20ideological%20compromise%20with%20Hindutva%20in%20these%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20Telangana%2C%20Yadav%20seems%20to%20be%20enamoured%20by%20the%20resurgence%20of%20the%20Congress%20vote%20share%20from%2028%25%20in%20the%202018%20election%20to%2039.4%25%20in%202023.%20Though%20this%20resurgence%20is%20positive%20for%20the%20Congress%2C%20it%20did%20not%20deter%20the%20double-digit%20growth%20rate%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20factor%20should%20not%20be%20missed%2C%20because%20it%20leads%20to%20false%20comfort%20that%20the%20South%20has%20closed%20its%20door%20to%20the%20BJP.%20In%20Telangana%2C%20the%20BJP%20procured%206.9%25%20votes%20and%2014.43%20lakh%20votes%20in%20the%202018%20elections.%20But%20in%202023%2C%20it%20doubled%20to%2013.90%25%20with%2032.51%20lakh%20votes.%20It%20has%20not%20only%20increased%20its%20seat%20share%20from%20one%20to%20eight%20but%20also%20stood%20second%20in%20more%20than%2018%20constituencies%20where%20it%20deployed%20nefarious%20tactics%20of%20communal%20polarisation.%20Thus%2C%20the%20growth%20rate%20of%20the%20BJP%20has%20doubled%20and%20its%20vote%20share%20is%20already%20a%20third%20of%20the%20victorious%20Congress%2C%20which%20is%20a%20dangerous%20portent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20it%20has%20a%20consolidated%20vote%20share%20of%2036%25%20in%20spite%20of%20its%20electoral%20defeat.%20One%20should%20also%20not%20close%20one%E2%80%99s%20eyes%20to%20the%20noise%20it%20is%20making%20in%20Dravidian%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20the%20growing%20number%20of%20Rashtriya%20Swayamsevak%20Sangh%20(RSS)%20shakhas%20in%20communist%20Kerala.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIs%20the%20vote%20share%20of%20Congress%20sufficient%20to%20stage%20a%20comeback%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20strange%20logic%20that%20Yadav%20offers%20is%20that%20since%20the%20difference%20in%20vote%20share%20between%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20is%20hardly%202%25%20to%204%25%2C%20one%20need%20not%20worry%20much%20about%20the%20loss%20of%20power.%20Since%20the%20Congress%20has%20reattained%20a%20vote%20share%20of%2040%25%2C%20it%20would%20be%20easy%20to%20stage%20a%20comeback.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAgain%20it%20is%20a%20mathematically%20correct%20but%20politically%20incorrect%20assessment%20of%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20situation%20in%20these%20three%20states.%20All%20of%20them%20are%20more%20or%20less%20bipolar%20states%2C%20with%20scarce%20influence%20of%20a%20third%20actor.%20These%20elections%20have%20shown%20that%20even%20the%20Dalit%2C%20Adivasi%2C%20and%20OBC%20social%20bases%20of%20smaller%20parties%20have%20been%20encroached%20upon%20by%20the%20BJP.%20In%20such%20a%20situation%2C%20stagnation%20of%20vote%20share%20is%20an%20indication%20that%20it%20is%20not%20only%20an%20electoral%20decline%20but%20a%20political%20decline.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym-300x194.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F09092514%2FF-aWeDnboAA_Tym-1024x662.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-684198%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22776%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EBJP%20supporters%20hold%20up%20Modi%20posters.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40narendramodi%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20analyses%20of%20vote%20shares%20of%20the%20BJP%20and%20Congress%20in%20the%20past%20five%20elections%20in%20these%20three%20states%2C%20barring%20Chhattisgarh%20in%202018%2C%20show%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20is%20growing%20whereas%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99s%20vote%20share%20is%20either%20stagnating%20or%20declining%20with%20one%20or%20two%20exceptions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20in%20Rajasthan%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20an%20average%20of%2039.88%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2045.17%25%20in%202013.%20Whereas%20the%20Congress%20shows%20an%20average%20of%2037.14%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2040.64%25%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20average%20is%2042.96%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2048.45%25%20in%202023.%20The%20Congress%20shows%20an%20average%20of%2036.42%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2041.35%25%20in%202018.%20In%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20an%20average%20of%2040.10%25%2C%20with%20a%20high%20of%2046.27%25%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOverall%20in%20bipolar%20elections%2C%20the%20Congress%20tends%20to%20lose%20its%20social%20base%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20which%20is%20obvious%20in%20these%20elections%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20even%20though%20theoretically%20a%2040%25%20vote%20share%20is%20enough%20to%20stage%20a%20comeback%2C%20the%20increasing%20loss%20of%20its%20social%20base%20to%20the%20BJP%20makes%20it%20impractical.%20The%20reason%20for%20this%20lies%20in%20the%20opportunist%2C%20Hindutva%2C%20and%20neoliberal%20politics%20of%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthree-things-bjps-definitive-victory-in-the-assembly-elections-tells-us%5C%22%3EThree%20Things%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Definitive%20Victory%20in%20the%20Assembly%20Elections%20Tells%20Us%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20these%20results%20have%20no%20impact%20on%202024%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Yadav%2C%20in%202003%2C%20even%20though%20the%20BJP%20won%20in%20the%20very%20same%20states%2C%20it%20lost%20the%202004%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20and%20while%20it%20lost%20these%20states%20in%202018%2C%20it%20won%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls.%20Hence%20one%20cannot%20extrapolate%20these%20results%20to%20have%20a%20bearing%20on%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections.%20Again%20it%20is%20a%20logically%20correct%20statement%2C%20but%20a%20historically%20and%20politically%20problematic%20conclusion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20advent%20of%20Hindutva%20and%20the%20communal%20polarisation%20of%20society%20and%20its%20intensification%20during%20the%20Modi%20regime%2C%20the%20RSS-BJP%20has%20cultivated%20an%20unchallenged%20Hindutva%20appeal%20among%20the%20Hindu%20electorate%20cutting%20across%20caste%2C%20community%2C%20class%2C%20gender%2C%20and%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh.jpg%201500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh-300x156.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh-768x400.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2018%2F06%2F01154842%2Fsangh-1024x533.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-255956%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22781%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ECredit%3A%20RSS%20website%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20RSS-BJP%20machinery%20has%20been%20creating%20false%20anxiety%20about%20the%20growing%20threat%20to%20the%20nation%20and%20Dharma%20which%20could%20only%20be%20thwarted%20by%20a%20%3Cem%3Evirat%20purush%3C%2Fem%3E%20like%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThus%2C%20of%20late%2C%20the%20elections%20have%20not%20become%20transactional%20affairs%20between%20the%20voter%20and%20the%20party%2C%20but%20they%20are%20becoming%20ideological%2C%20especially%20between%20the%20BJP%20voters%20and%20the%20party.%20Thus%2C%20whatever%20may%20be%20the%20results%20in%20the%20state%20elections%2C%20at%20least%20from%202013%2C%20the%20people%20of%20these%20three%20states%2C%20and%20those%20in%20the%20Hindi%20belt%20in%20general%2C%20have%20overwhelmingly%20elected%20the%20BJP%20both%20in%202014%20and%202019.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20results%20will%20definitely%20have%20an%20impact%20on%20the%20neighbouring%20Hindi%20states%2C%20which%20together%20account%20for%20240%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20%E2%80%98Modi%20magic%E2%80%99%20but%20the%20colossal%20political%20failure%20of%20the%20Congress%20and%20the%20opposition%20in%20offering%20themselves%20as%20a%20credible%20alternative.%20Hence%20ridiculing%20this%20sad%20phenomenon%20as%20%E2%80%98impossible%20magic%E2%80%99%20is%20neither%20a%20serious%20analysis%20nor%20a%20serious%20critique.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWill%20the%20BJP%20lose%2019%20seats%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20if%20the%20same%20pattern%20repeats%20in%202024%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Yadav%2C%20if%20the%20same%20pattern%20of%20voting%20is%20repeated%20in%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20the%20BJP%20would%20lose%2019%20seats%20and%20Congress%20would%20gain%2022%20seats.%20For%20such%20a%20thing%20to%20happen%2C%20the%20Congress%20should%20ensure%20that%20it%20repeats%20the%20same%20performance%20in%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETake%20for%20example%20the%202019%20elections.%20Rajasthan%20has%2025%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%2C%20Congress%20got%20more%20votes%20and%20seats%20in%20the%202018%20assembly%20elections%2C%20but%20could%20not%20win%20even%20one%20seat%20there.%20All%2025%20went%20to%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA).%20In%20Chhattisgarh%2C%20where%20the%20Congress%20got%2010%25%20more%20votes%20than%20the%20BJP%20in%20the%202018%20assembly%20elections%2C%20it%20could%20win%20only%20two%20Lok%20Sabha%20seats%20%E2%80%93%20the%20BJP%20got%20the%20remaining%20nine.%20In%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20the%20Congress%20won%20only%20one%20and%20the%20rest%2028%20were%20won%20by%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMere%20extrapolation%20of%20votes%20provides%20only%20mathematical%20solutions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20history%20and%20politics%20of%20these%20states%20demand%20introspection%20and%20rupture%20with%20the%20past%20by%20the%20Congress%20to%20stage%20a%20comeback.%20But%2C%20the%20Congress%20party%20has%20not%20shown%20any%20inclination%20or%20a%20rupture%20from%20its%20soft%20Hindutva%20and%20neoliberal%20politics%20either%20in%20its%20campaign%20or%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20situation%2C%20Congress%20looks%20like%20a%20party%20with%20the%20same%20fibre%20as%20the%20BJP%20but%20with%20a%20different%20colour.%20Without%20a%20radical%20transformation%20of%20Congress%20politically%2C%20ideologically%20and%20organisationally%2C%20leave%20alone%20defeating%20the%20BJP%2C%20the%20survival%20of%20the%20Congress%20itself%20would%20become%20difficult.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENot%20warning%20the%20party%20and%20nation%20about%20this%20possibility%20would%20be%20a%20disservice%20to%20both.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%2C%20as%20a%20social%20activist%20engaged%20in%20anti-fascist%20battles%20in%20Karnataka%2C%20have%20always%20shared%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20dreams%20respectfully%2C%20though%20not%20his%20shifting%20political%20strategies.%20But%20this%20analysis%20took%20me%20by%20surprise%20and%20disbelief.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Gramsci%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CPessimism%20of%20the%20intellect%20and%20optimism%20of%20the%20will%E2%80%9D%20is%20the%20need%20of%20the%20hour%20in%20these%20times%20of%20gloom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fshivasundar%5C%22%3EShivasundar%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20an%20activist%20and%20a%20freelance%20journalist%20based%20in%20Bangalore.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EYogendra%20Yadav%E2%80%99s%20response%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20agree%20with%20most%20of%20the%20substantive%20points%20made%20by%20Mr%20Shivasundar.%20So%20there%20isn%E2%80%99t%20much%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98debate%E2%80%99%20between%20us.%20If%20there%20is%20a%20difference%20in%20emphasis%2C%20it%20is%20because%20he%20may%20have%20missed%20the%20whole%20point%20of%20my%20video%20(which%20was%20translated%20from%20Hindi%20and%20converted%20into%20a%20write-up).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20was%20responding%20to%20the%20widespread%20propaganda%20that%20the%20BJP%20has%20drummed%20up%20with%20the%20help%20of%20darbari%20media%3A%20that%20the%20hat-trick%20in%20the%20three%20North%20Indian%20states%20is%20bound%20to%20lead%20to%20a%20hat-trick%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%2C%20that%202024%20is%20now%20a%20closed%20contest%2C%20that%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20victory%20is%20inevitable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20the%20facts%20and%20figures%20I%20presented%20exposed%20the%20falsity%20of%20this%20propaganda.%20My%20point%20is%20that%20this%20is%20not%20yet%20a%20closed%20contest%2C%20that%20the%20gap%20in%20votes%20is%20not%20impossible%20to%20overcome%2C%20that%20if%20the%20opposition%20manages%20to%20hold%20on%20to%20the%20votes%20that%20it%20got%20even%20in%20this%20defeat%20this%20would%20set%20the%20BJP%20back%2C%20that%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20can%20be%20different%20from%20Vidhan%20Sabha%20outcomes.%20Therefore%202024%20is%20not%20a%20done%20deal%20yet.%20I%20hope%20Mr%20Shivasundar%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20disagree.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20have%20nowhere%20suggested%20that%20this%20is%20going%20to%20be%20easy%2C%20let%20alone%20inevitable.%20Of%20course%2C%20this%20would%20require%20introspection%2C%20realignment%20and%20hard%20work%20on%20the%20ground%20over%20the%20next%20few%20months.%20But%20that%20is%20the%20subject%20matter%20of%20another%20video.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1701950437000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2017%2F11%2FModi-Shah.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdebate-yogendra-yadav-analysis-bjp-wins-assembly-polls-misleading%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Yadav%20had%20written%20that%20'BJP's%20victory%20is%20not%20so%20big%2C%20and%20Congress%20fall%20is%20not%20so%20deep'.%20Such%20a%20view%20is%20nothing%20but%20a%20false%20comfort.%20If%20the%20Congress%20does%20not%20honestly%20address%20the%20issues%20it%20is%20facing%2C%20putting%20up%20a%20good%20fight%20in%202024%20will%20be%20extremely%20difficult.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdebate-yogendra-yadav-analysis-bjp-wins-assembly-polls-misleading%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Poorna%20Swami%E2%80%99s%20Translation%20of%20the%20Poem%20%E2%80%98Falasteeni%E2%80%99%20Awarded%20the%202023%20Jawad%20Memorial%20Prize%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F07170656%2Fimage-1582.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%202023%20edition%20of%20the%20Jawad%20Memorial%20Prize%20for%20Urdu-English%20Translation%20has%20been%20awarded%20to%20Poorna%20Swami%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20the%20poem%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EFalasteeni%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(%E2%80%98Palestinian%E2%80%99)%20by%20Fehmida%20Riaz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20runner-up%20prize%20has%20been%20awarded%20to%20Mohd%20Aqib%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EPabandi%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20(%E2%80%98Prohibition%E2%80%99)%20by%20Ahmed%20Nadim%20Qasmi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20jury%20noted%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20poem%20%E2%80%98Palestinian%E2%80%99%20translated%20its%20source%20material%20with%20fidelity%2C%20but%20without%20sacrificing%20a%20poetic%20sensibility%20of%20its%20own.%20Among%20the%20poems%20we%20examined%2C%20it%20presented%20a%20shining%20example%20of%20how%20good%20translation%20threads%20the%20needle%20between%20minimising%20the%20loss%20of%20original%20metaphor%20and%20maximising%20the%20lyrical%20quality%20of%20the%20output%20language.%20The%20quality%20of%20submitted%20translations%20was%20consistently%20good%2C%20making%20for%20a%20tough%20choice%20but%2C%20ultimately%2C%20this%20poem%20truly%20stood%20out.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20runner-up%2C%20%E2%80%98Prohibition%2C%E2%80%99%20is%20a%20short%20poem%20and%20the%20translator%20has%20effectively%20communicated%20its%20resistance%20against%20censorship%20and%20prohibition.%20The%20jury%20found%20the%20poem%E2%80%99s%20imagery%20of%20rolling%20pearls%20and%20drops%20falling%20on%20raging%20fires%20most%20evocative%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPoorna%20Swami%E2%80%99s%20essays%20and%20reportage%20have%20appeared%20in%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Caravan%2C%20Open%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20%3Cem%3ELondon%20Review%20of%20Books%3C%2Fem%3E%20(web)%2C%20among%20others.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPreviously%20holding%20the%20position%20of%20India%20editor-at-large%20at%20the%20international%20translation%20quarterly%20%3Cem%3EAsymptote%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20Swami%20also%20co-edited%20the%20journal%E2%80%99s%20first%20feature%20on%20Indian%20language%20poetry%20translated%20into%20English.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECurrently%2C%20she%20is%20pursuing%20her%20PhD%20in%20the%20Department%20of%20South%20Asian%20Studies%20at%20Harvard%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMohd%20Aqib%20is%20a%20University%20Grants%20Commission%20junior%20research%20fellow%20and%20a%20PhD%20candidate%20at%20the%20Department%20of%20English%20at%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%20university.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fmirza-ghalib-temple-lamp-maaz-bin-bilal-review%5C%22%3E%20A%20Translation%20of%20Ghalib%E2%80%99s%20Persian%20Ode%20to%20Banaras%20Reminds%20Us%20of%20What%20Makes%20Us%20Hindustani%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Jawad%20Memorial%20Prize%20gets%20its%20name%20from%20Ali%20Jawad%20Zaidi%2C%20an%20Urdu%20poet%20and%20scholar%20and%20winner%20of%20several%20awards%20including%20the%20Padma%20Shri%2C%20the%20Ghalib%20award%2C%20Mir%20Anis%20award%20among%20others.%20The%20Prize%20was%20initiated%20shortly%20after%20his%20birth%20centenary%20in%202016%20to%20honour%20his%20legacy%20of%20literature%20that%20served%20as%20a%20bridge%20between%20languages%2C%20cultures%20and%20histories.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20several%20books%20of%20prose%20and%20poetry%2C%20Zaidi%20published%20several%20scholarly%20works%20such%20as%20A%20History%20of%20Urdu%20Literature%2C%20Uttar%20Pradesh%20ke%20Marsiyago%20and%20Taarikh-e-Mushayara%2C%20all%20of%20which%20contributed%20to%20his%20tireless%20efforts%20towards%20making%20Urdu%20literature%20accessible%20to%20all%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20language%20they%20speak.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judges%20for%20this%20year%E2%80%99s%20prize%20were%20literary%20critic%20and%20translator%20Anisur%20Rahman%20as%20well%20as%20author%20Raza%20Mir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormerly%20a%20professor%20of%20English%20at%20Jamia%20Millia%20Islamia%2C%20and%20a%20senior%20advisor%20at%20Rekhta%20Foundation%2C%20Rahman%20has%20worked%20and%20published%20in%20the%20areas%20of%20comparative%2C%20translation%2C%20postcolonial%2C%20and%20Urdu%20studies.%20His%20recent%20publications%20include%20%3Cem%3EEarthenware%3A%20Sixty%20Poems%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Rubric%20Publishing%2C%202018)%2C%20%3Cem%3EIn%20Translation%3A%20Positions%20and%20Paradigms%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Orient%20Blackswan%2C%202019)%2C%20%3Cem%3ESocioliterary%20Cultures%20in%20South%20Asia%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Niyogi%20Books%2C%202019)%2C%20%3Cem%3EHazaaron%20Khwahishein%20Aisi%3A%20The%20Wonderful%20World%20of%20Urdu%20Ghazals%3C%2Fem%3E%20(HarperCollins%2C%202019)%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3EHazaar%20Rang%20Shaairi%3A%20The%20Wonderful%20World%20of%20the%20Urdu%20Nazm%3C%2Fem%3E%20(HarperCollins%202022).%20Rahman%20has%20been%20a%20Shastri%20Fellow%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Alberta%2C%20Canada%20(2001-2002)%20and%20a%20Visiting%20Scholar%20at%20Purdue%20University%2C%20US%20(2007).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERaza%20Mir%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20management%20at%20William%20Paterson%20University%20in%20the%20US.%20His%20latest%20books%20are%20%3Cem%3EIqbal%3A%20Poet%20of%20the%20East%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Penguin%2C%202022)%20and%20%3Cem%3EMurder%20at%20the%20Mushaira%3C%2Fem%3E%20(Aleph%202021).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fwhen-the-moon-gets-caught-in-the-barbed-wire-over-the-prison-wall-varavara-rao-poetry%5C%22%3EWhen%20the%20Moon%20Gets%20Caught%20in%20the%20Barbed%20Wire%2C%20Over%20the%20Prison%20Wall%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPrevious%20winners%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202022%20prize%20went%20to%20Sana%20R.%20Chaudhry%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EPyaare%20Ustaad%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20written%20by%20Julien%20Columeau.%20The%20runner-up%20prize%20was%20shared%20by%20Shama%20Askari%20for%20her%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98Begum%E2%80%99%20by%20Ibn%20e%20Sai%E2%80%99d%3B%20and%20Sabyn%20Javeri%20for%20%E2%80%98The%20Busy%20Woman%2C%E2%80%99%20a%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EMasroof%20Aurat%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20by%20Khalida%20Hussain.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202021%20prize%20was%20shared%20by%20Aalim%20Akhtar%20for%20his%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EHari%20Bol%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20by%20Zakia%20Mashhadi%2C%20and%20Bilal%20Tanweer%20for%20%E2%80%98Parasite%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3EKeera%3C%2Fem%3E)%20written%20by%20Bilal%20Hasan%20Minto.%20There%20was%20a%20jury%20commendation%20for%20Nazia%20Akhtar%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3EChhottam%20Jaan%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%98%20by%20Zeenath%20Sajida%20and%20Fathima%20M.%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98Shadows%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3ESaaye%3C%2Fem%3E)%20by%20Khalid%20Jawed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202020%20winner%20was%20Haider%20Shahbaz%E2%80%99s%20translation%20of%20%E2%80%98The%20Sea%E2%80%99%20by%20Khalida%20Hussain.%20There%20was%20no%20runner-up.%20However%2C%20there%20was%20a%20jury%20commendation%20for%20%E2%80%98Tiffin%20Carrier%E2%80%99%20by%20Muneera%20Surati%2C%20translated%20by%20the%20author